#MEM id=capital-allocation source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/operating-system/capital-allocation/SKILL.md savings=12%
M||tx|---
M||name|capital-allocation
M||desc|Buffett's concentration doctrine for yv's budget. When to double down on one vt vs. split resources. Prevents default equal allocation when ROI data points clearly in one direction.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|Buffett doesn't diversify by default — he concentrates capital on the highest-conviction opportunity. Equal budget allocation btw two vt w/ unequal ROI is not neutral. It is a choice to underinvest in what's working and keep alive what isn't.
M|Purp|tx|fx applies this doctrine every time budget is discussed across vt or channels.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|When|it|Any cross-vt budget discussion
M|When|it|Quarterly budget reviews
M|When|it|When mc asks how to split budget btw nz and hb
M|When|it|When one vt is significantly outperforming the other on ROI signals
M|When|it|When a channel is clearly outperforming others within a single vt
M|When|tx|---
